---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ServiceCard from '../../components/ServiceCard.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { WEB_SERVICES } from '../../lib/site';

const title = 'Website development services';
const description =
  'Apriori Studio designs and builds e-commerce stores, marketing sites, and custom web applications. End-to-end: domain, hosting, design, code, launch, and support.';
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-5 py-10 md:py-14">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { href: '/', label: 'Home' },
      { href: '/web', label: 'Websites' },
    ]} />

    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Websites that work for the people who use them
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] max-w-2xl">
        Whatever you need a website for — selling, telling a story, running a business behind
        the scenes — we've probably built it before. Pick a category to see how we approach it.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-5 mb-14">
      {WEB_SERVICES.map((s) => (
        <ServiceCard href={s.href} title={s.title} blurb={s.blurb} />
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose-body max-w-3xl">
      <h2>What "end-to-end" actually means</h2>
      <p>
        Most agencies hand you a Figma file and walk away. Or they write code but expect you to
        sort out hosting yourself. Or they launch the site and never tell you the SSL certificate
        renews in ninety days. Apriori Studio is set up differently — we cover everything between
        "I have an idea" and "the site is live and looked after."
      </p>

      <h3>Picking the right domain</h3>
      <p>
        We help you choose and register your domain through a registrar that won't trap you with
        hidden renewal fees, won't sell your contact details to spammers, and gives you proper API
        access if you ever want to automate DNS later. We set up email-related DNS records (SPF,
        DKIM, DMARC) so messages from your domain don't end up in junk.
      </p>

      <h3>Hosting that fits</h3>
      <p>
        For a static marketing site, we use a small VPS or a free CDN — no point paying for
        Kubernetes when nginx will do. For an e-commerce store, we'll match the hosting to your
        traffic profile. For a SaaS app with a real database, we'll set up a proper server with
        backups, monitoring, and a deploy pipeline. We'll explain why we picked what we picked,
        and what it would cost to scale up later.
      </p>

      <h3>Design that's about your users, not our portfolio</h3>
      <p>
        We don't do design awards. We design for the people clicking buttons. That means clear
        information hierarchy, fast loading on slow phones, accessible to keyboard users and screen
        readers, and consistent across browsers. If you have brand guidelines, we follow them. If
        you don't, we help you build a small set that's easy to maintain.
      </p>

      <h3>Code that the next developer can read</h3>
      <p>
        Whether we use Astro, Next.js, Laravel, or whatever else fits the job, we write code that
        someone else could pick up six months later without crying. Sensible names, clear file
        structure, no clever tricks. We use the boring, well-documented option over the trendy one
        unless there's a real reason.
      </p>

      <h3>Integrations and analytics</h3>
      <p>
        Stripe, PayPal, MailChimp, Google Analytics, Plausible, Sentry, Cloudflare, Algolia,
        third-party CRMs — we've integrated with most of the common services. We'll tell you which
        of them you actually need at your stage, and which can wait until you have real users.
      </p>

      <h3>Launch and after</h3>
      <p>
        Going live is the start, not the finish. We monitor uptime, keep dependencies up to date,
        renew certificates automatically, and back up data regularly. If something breaks on a
        Saturday, you have a person to call — not a ticketing portal.
      </p>

      <h2>How a project usually goes</h2>
      <p>
        We start with a short conversation — sometimes a thirty-minute call is enough — to figure
        out what you need and whether we're the right people for it. If it's a fit, we send a
        written quote with a fixed scope, fixed price, and a realistic timeline. If we're not the
        right fit, we'll say so, and where possible we'll suggest someone who is.
      </p>
      <p>
        Once we start, we share progress in writing every few days. You see the work as it goes,
        not just at a final reveal. If something needs changing, we change it without drama. We
        ship to a staging URL early so you can click through it on your own phone in real
        conditions.
      </p>

      <h2>Pricing, in plain numbers</h2>
      <p>
        A small marketing site (5-8 pages, no e-commerce) typically lands between £2,500 and
        £6,000, depending on how much custom design and copywriting you need. An e-commerce store
        starts around £5,000 and goes up with the catalogue size and integrations. A SaaS or web
        app is quoted per project — there's no honest one-size-fits-all number for those. Hosting
        and domain run separately and we'll set them up in your name, on your accounts, so nothing
        is locked to us.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
